reviewText: Wow, this movie wasn't what I expected at all. Any movie that is dialogue driven and holds up is alright in my book. It's hard to tell what's real and what's not for most of this movie. I'm a big fan of the old Twilight Zone show and this reminded me of that.
Title: N/A

reviewText: This is a hard look inside the mind of a mentally ill person--rough to take and not much "fun," but well-made and well-acted on a limited budget.  For a one-room, three actor ensemble piece, it's got plenty of action, although a lot of it's like chalk on a blackboard.  The screws tighten and so do the nerves.  It's never quite clear what's real and what isn't, and for the most part you want to just flee, but you can't, and you can't look away...like a bad accident in slow motion.  You have been warned.
summary: Hard to watch, hard to look away

reviewText: I thought this was an original take on a familiar story: guy loses everything & might be crazy.  It was dark, and really sucks you in...I was really worried about what those two were going to do with that dead girl!  The suspense is great, and you get very attached to the characters.  Good stuff.

reviewText: You don't know where this movie is going to take you until the end.  The lead character may or may not be crazy, but there is a dead girl that just appears & he doesn't know where she came from.  His bff has to help him figure out what to do with the body, & should probably win an award for best friend EVER.  It really kept me guessing, I'm glad I watched it.
